                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d547">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/9–2650: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-09-26T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >September 26, 1950—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>151. Although <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> appreciates difficulties
                    involved, in view apparent possibility imminent return of <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Govt to Seoul request you make every effort
                    discourage Rhee or other <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> spokesmen making
                    pronouncements re <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>’s unilateral extension
                    authority north 38°. This matter being considered highest Govt levels; also of
                    vital concern to all UN member states. Any unilateral public statement from
                        <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> can only have harmful effect on attitude
                    UN members. <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> delegation in confidential
                    discussions with other UN delegations is at this time most effective method
                    conveying <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> views. You shld emphasize to Rhee
                    his cooperation with UN at this time of utmost importance to future <gloss
                        target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
